tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, and severe proteinuria with low urine specific gravity, suggesting nephrotic syndrome or advanced kidney disease. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor) may indicate urinary tract pathology. High urine ketones and glucose, with low HbA1c, are unusual and may reflect acute metabolic disturbance. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended.
